<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d304">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">195.7 <hi rend="italic">Jean
                                    Nicolet</hi>/5–2645: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-26">May 26,
                                    1945</date>.<lb/>[Received May 26—11 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2920. Am[erican] Interests—Japan. Department’s 4184, December
                                    12.<note n="10" xml:id="d304fn1">
                                    <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_1176">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 1176</ref>.</note> Swiss
                                note May 25 gives in translation following Japanese reply
                                telegraphed May 24 by Swiss Legation, Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Serious investigations made by competent authorities were
                                        unable disclose any act corresponding similar accident.
                                        Japanese Government takes occasion reaffirm that all
                                        Japanese warships, boats and vessels strictly observe laws
                                        of war.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>